author: Michele Amabile Angermiller
title: 'The Voice' Winner Sundance Head Signs With Republic Records
text:
Posted by Sundance Head on Friday, February 3, 2017 

Sundance Head -- who competed as part of Blake Shelton’s team and will open for his coach beginning Feb. 12 on tour -- has also signed with Dreamcatcher Management, Loeb & Loeb for legal representation and CAA for booking appearances. 
The Texas native -- who also competed on the sixth season of American Idol -- was crowned the winner of The Voice after performing his original song “Darlin’ Don’t Go” in the finals.
